WEBVTT

00:00:12.583 --> 00:00:16.542
"June 24, 2024"       "Floor 48: Lindas"

00:00:25.375 --> 00:00:26.792
That'll do it.

00:00:29.167 --> 00:00:30.667
Thanks, Liz!

00:00:31.417 --> 00:00:32.667
You're welcome.

00:00:34.875 --> 00:00:37.375
Aren't you going hunting
with the guild today?

00:00:39.083 --> 00:00:40.958
I took the day off.

00:00:40.958 --> 00:00:43.083
I'm meeting someone, you see.

00:00:47.417 --> 00:00:49.125
So that's it.

00:00:49.125 --> 00:00:50.792
Wh-What?

00:00:53.458 --> 00:00:55.000
I have to go!

00:00:58.000 --> 00:01:00.625
You've found something
important to you, haven't you?

00:01:01.875 --> 00:01:03.042
Did you say something?

00:01:03.417 --> 00:01:05.500
Nope, nothing at all.

00:01:05.500 --> 00:01:07.042
Just make sure it works out, okay?

00:01:07.042 --> 00:01:09.167
It isn't like that!

00:01:09.167 --> 00:01:10.458
Anyway, see you.

00:01:19.792 --> 00:01:22.792
I wonder if I'll ever
find something too?

00:01:36.375 --> 00:01:40.792
<i>The cowardly past that I'd acknowledged</i>

00:01:41.125 --> 00:01:46.583
<i>Still not understanding why,</i>

00:01:46.917 --> 00:01:57.500
<i>I stand behind myself, scared</i>
<i>Projecting reality onto today</i>

00:01:57.917 --> 00:02:02.917
<i>I've drawn so many skies</i>

00:02:03.250 --> 00:02:07.583
<i>This must be my fleeting heart</i>

00:02:07.917 --> 00:02:10.292
<i>Out of control</i>

00:02:10.625 --> 00:02:15.875
<i>In my dreams, this body soars so high</i>

00:02:16.208 --> 00:02:21.042
<i>And it can brush away any fears that cling to me</i>

00:02:21.375 --> 00:02:27.542
<i>Asleep inside me, these budding</i>
<i>feelings start to expand</i>

00:02:27.833 --> 00:02:31.458
<i>I realize this, weak as I am...</i>
<i>As long as I had you</i>

00:02:31.792 --> 00:02:36.750
<i>I could stay strong in this dark world</i>

00:02:37.083 --> 00:02:42.792
<i>My heart will dream a long dream forever</i>

00:02:43.792 --> 00:02:46.250
<i>I want to always be with you</i>

00:02:46.583 --> 00:02:51.917
<i>I'll give you everything I have...</i>

00:02:55.083 --> 00:02:59.083
"The Temperature of the Heart"

00:03:10.000 --> 00:03:12.000
So-so, I guess...

00:03:14.875 --> 00:03:17.292
Dealing with customers is
part of my job, too.

00:03:20.625 --> 00:03:21.625
Okay!

00:03:25.458 --> 00:03:27.500
Welcome to Lisbeth's Smith Shop!

00:03:28.833 --> 00:03:30.583
U-Uh...

00:03:30.583 --> 00:03:33.000
I'd like to order a
custom-made weapon.

00:03:37.125 --> 00:03:39.958
<i>Does he have enough money?</i>

00:03:40.625 --> 00:03:44.250
At the moment,
metal prices are high.

00:03:44.250 --> 00:03:46.333
Don't worry about the cost.

00:03:46.333 --> 00:03:49.625
I just want the best sword
you can make right now.

00:03:49.625 --> 00:03:51.583
That's somewhat vague.

00:03:51.583 --> 00:03:55.250
You'll have to give me an idea
of your target quality level.

00:03:55.250 --> 00:03:56.958
Oh, I see.

00:03:57.458 --> 00:04:01.667
Then something of the same
quality as this or better?

00:04:05.667 --> 00:04:07.333
An Elucidator...

00:04:07.333 --> 00:04:11.375
It's a beast of a magic sword
obtainable from monster drops.

00:04:12.250 --> 00:04:13.750
Can you make one?

00:04:17.042 --> 00:04:18.667
How about this one?

00:04:18.667 --> 00:04:21.833
It's the best I've ever forged.
My masterpiece!

00:04:23.375 --> 00:04:25.125
It's a little light...

00:04:25.750 --> 00:04:28.500
Well, I did use a speed-type
metal to forge it.

00:04:29.250 --> 00:04:31.250
Would you mind if I tested it?

00:04:31.250 --> 00:04:32.625
Test it?

00:04:32.625 --> 00:04:33.833
You know, its durability.

00:04:35.083 --> 00:04:36.750
H-Hey!

00:04:36.750 --> 00:04:39.500
Your sword will break
in two if you do that!

00:04:39.500 --> 00:04:42.125
If that happens,
it'll just be... too bad!

00:04:55.667 --> 00:04:57.833
Irreparable...

00:05:07.750 --> 00:05:09.792
What were you thinking?

00:05:09.792 --> 00:05:10.917
Sorry!

00:05:10.917 --> 00:05:13.875
I never thought that yours
would be the one to break...

00:05:13.875 --> 00:05:17.833
Is that your way of saying that my
sword was lamer than you expected?

00:05:19.167 --> 00:05:20.458
Yeah, I guess.

00:05:22.500 --> 00:05:25.708
Just so we're clear,
if I had the materials,

00:05:25.708 --> 00:05:30.750
I could make tons of swords that
would snap yours like a twig!

00:05:32.458 --> 00:05:34.542
I'd really love to order one.

00:05:34.542 --> 00:05:36.833
Something that could snap
this one like a twig!

00:05:37.000 --> 00:05:40.583
I-If you're gonna be like that, then you'll
have to help me every step of the way!

00:05:40.583 --> 00:05:41.500
Every step of the way?

00:05:41.500 --> 00:05:44.083
Right, starting with
obtaining the metal.

00:05:44.667 --> 00:05:46.500
I'll be just fine on my own.

00:05:46.500 --> 00:05:48.750
I'd rather not have you
slowing me down.

00:05:48.750 --> 00:05:51.000
Don't you insult me.

00:05:51.000 --> 00:05:53.500
Believe it or not,
I'm an expert mace user.

00:05:53.500 --> 00:05:56.375
Then where do we find the metal?

00:05:56.750 --> 00:06:01.417
On floor 55, there's supposedly a dragon
that eats crystals on the Western Mountain.

00:06:01.833 --> 00:06:05.375
According to the rumor, it stores
rare metal inside its body.

00:06:05.375 --> 00:06:07.125
Floor 55, huh?

00:06:07.708 --> 00:06:09.958
--I should probably go--
--Furthermore, to get the metal,

00:06:09.958 --> 00:06:12.875
you need a master smith with you.

00:06:12.875 --> 00:06:14.875
Still want to go alone?

00:06:22.458 --> 00:06:24.708
Just keep quiet and
stay out of the way.

00:06:24.708 --> 00:06:26.000
Hey!

00:06:26.000 --> 00:06:27.750
My name's Kirito.

00:06:27.750 --> 00:06:30.250
Until we make that sword,
I guess we'll be partying up.

00:06:30.250 --> 00:06:31.833
Okay, Kirito!

00:06:31.833 --> 00:06:33.500
You're being rather curt...

00:06:33.500 --> 00:06:34.625
Well, whatever.

00:06:35.042 --> 00:06:36.708
Lisbeth.

00:06:45.958 --> 00:06:48.083
"Floor 55: Western Mountain"

00:06:48.083 --> 00:06:49.833
"Floor 55: Western Mountain"
It's cold...

00:06:49.833 --> 00:06:52.000
Don't you have any extra clothing?

00:06:52.000 --> 00:06:55.292
I didn't know floor 55
was an ice and snow zone!

00:07:00.250 --> 00:07:02.125
Are you going to be
okay without this?

00:07:02.125 --> 00:07:04.375
I've had more training than you.

00:07:05.083 --> 00:07:07.583
You really know how to
piss me off every time!

00:07:09.750 --> 00:07:11.042
It's warm.

00:07:12.542 --> 00:07:15.417
<i>I can't believe I'm out here</i>
<i>all alone with this guy.</i>

00:07:16.250 --> 00:07:18.083
<i>Things are certainly getting weird...</i>

00:07:18.667 --> 00:07:20.333
What's wrong, Lisbeth?

00:07:20.333 --> 00:07:21.792
Giving up already?

00:07:21.792 --> 00:07:23.208
I'm still going strong!

00:07:23.208 --> 00:07:26.708
And if you're going to be so familiar
anyway, just call me Liz.

00:07:26.708 --> 00:07:28.917
Right, right... Got it, Liz.

00:07:28.917 --> 00:07:30.333
Don't get carried away!

00:07:43.417 --> 00:07:45.333
It's beautiful!

00:07:48.375 --> 00:07:50.083
What are you doing?

00:07:50.083 --> 00:07:52.167
Get your teleport crystal ready.

00:07:52.917 --> 00:07:54.500
I know.

00:07:54.500 --> 00:07:56.667
Also, I'm going to handle
this part alone.

00:07:57.250 --> 00:07:58.833
Once the dragon appears,

00:07:58.833 --> 00:08:01.375
hide behind one of those
crystals over there.

00:08:01.375 --> 00:08:02.875
Don't come out, no matter what.

00:08:02.875 --> 00:08:04.125
Oh, come on!

00:08:04.125 --> 00:08:06.417
I'm no newbie either, you know!
So I'll help you--

00:08:06.417 --> 00:08:07.417
No!

00:08:14.208 --> 00:08:15.833
Good.

00:08:15.833 --> 00:08:17.125
All right. Let's get going.

00:08:27.792 --> 00:08:29.000
Hide yourself there!

00:08:43.792 --> 00:08:45.458
It's a breath attack! Dodge!

00:08:53.208 --> 00:08:54.542
<i>Wow...</i>

00:08:55.542 --> 00:08:57.292
<i>All with that thin weapon?</i>

00:08:57.292 --> 00:08:59.125
<i>Who in the world is he?</i>

00:09:08.667 --> 00:09:11.125
Come on, finish him off already!

00:09:11.125 --> 00:09:11.792
You idiot!

00:09:11.792 --> 00:09:13.333
Don't come out yet!

00:09:15.250 --> 00:09:17.708
What's the big deal?
It's over now--

00:09:22.042 --> 00:09:23.042
Liz!

00:09:30.167 --> 00:09:32.417
No!

00:09:34.083 --> 00:09:35.583
Liz, hang on!

00:09:52.458 --> 00:09:54.125
So you're alive...

00:09:56.375 --> 00:09:58.417
Yeah, I'm alive.

00:10:01.167 --> 00:10:03.042
Drink one of these, just in case.

00:10:03.375 --> 00:10:04.375
Okay.

00:10:14.833 --> 00:10:18.708
Um, thank you for saving me.

00:10:18.708 --> 00:10:21.250
It's a little too early
to thank me.

00:10:21.250 --> 00:10:23.000
How are we gonna
get out of here?

00:10:23.333 --> 00:10:26.000
Huh? We can just
teleport, right?

00:10:27.458 --> 00:10:29.083
Teleport: Lindas!

00:10:31.125 --> 00:10:32.542
No way...

00:10:32.542 --> 00:10:36.542
If we can't use crystals, that means
there should be another way.

00:10:36.542 --> 00:10:38.750
We don't know that.

00:10:38.750 --> 00:10:42.583
This could be a trap meant to kill
people with 100% certainty!

00:10:42.583 --> 00:10:44.667
I see... That's a good point.

00:10:46.167 --> 00:10:47.292
Listen, you...

00:10:47.292 --> 00:10:49.125
At least try to cheer me up!

00:10:49.125 --> 00:10:50.750
I have one idea.

00:10:50.750 --> 00:10:51.917
Really?

00:10:52.250 --> 00:10:54.917
Yeah, to run up the wall.

00:10:58.125 --> 00:10:59.292
Are you stupid?

00:11:00.083 --> 00:11:02.125
Why don't we find out
if I'm stupid or not?

00:11:06.958 --> 00:11:08.292
Unbelievable...

00:11:19.167 --> 00:11:22.250
If I had a little more room to get
a running start, I would've made it.

00:11:22.750 --> 00:11:24.833
Yeah, in your dreams.

00:11:30.333 --> 00:11:32.375
What a strange feeling.

00:11:32.375 --> 00:11:34.167
This would never happen in real life.

00:11:34.542 --> 00:11:38.042
Sleeping next to someone
I just met for the first time

00:11:38.042 --> 00:11:39.625
in a place I've never been before.

00:11:40.500 --> 00:11:42.875
Not only that, but you started
running up the wall!

00:11:43.375 --> 00:11:44.958
You really are a weirdo.

00:11:45.583 --> 00:11:46.958
Well, excuse me.

00:11:52.583 --> 00:11:54.083
Hey, Kirito...

00:11:54.083 --> 00:11:55.292
Can I ask you something?

00:11:55.292 --> 00:11:57.042
You're being so formal. What is it?

00:11:57.833 --> 00:12:00.500
Back then, why did you save me?

00:12:02.417 --> 00:12:04.917
Because I'd much rather
die with someone

00:12:05.625 --> 00:12:07.875
than let that person die
before my eyes.

00:12:08.542 --> 00:12:11.458
Even more so if she's
a girl like you, Liz.

00:12:12.792 --> 00:12:14.708
You really are an idiot.

00:12:14.708 --> 00:12:17.042
No one else would think that way.

00:12:21.792 --> 00:12:22.917
Hey...

00:12:23.375 --> 00:12:24.625
Hold my hand?

00:12:31.583 --> 00:12:32.583
Okay.

00:12:41.083 --> 00:12:42.250
It's warm.

00:12:45.083 --> 00:12:48.792
Even though you and I are
both data in a virtual world...

00:12:49.500 --> 00:12:50.500
Liz...

00:13:07.500 --> 00:13:08.500
Huh?

00:13:17.083 --> 00:13:18.292
What are you doing?

00:13:19.083 --> 00:13:20.167
Look at this.

00:13:23.083 --> 00:13:24.208
"Crystallite Ingot"

00:13:24.208 --> 00:13:26.083
"Crystallite Ingot"
Wait... Could this be...

00:13:26.083 --> 00:13:29.917
"Crystallite Ingot"
Yeah, it must be the metal we came to get.

00:13:29.917 --> 00:13:33.875
The dragon nibbles on the crystals,
producing this in its stomach.

00:13:35.750 --> 00:13:37.500
No wonder no one
can ever find any!

00:13:37.500 --> 00:13:38.542
You did it.

00:13:39.250 --> 00:13:41.250
But what's it doing here?

00:13:41.250 --> 00:13:43.625
This hole isn't a trap.

00:13:43.625 --> 00:13:45.208
It's the dragon's nest.

00:13:46.375 --> 00:13:50.500
In other words, that ingot is
the dragon's excrement.

00:13:50.500 --> 00:13:51.500
It's poop.

00:13:56.458 --> 00:13:59.833
Anyway, this means that
we've achieved our goal.

00:13:59.833 --> 00:14:00.833
All that's left is...

00:14:03.375 --> 00:14:06.375
Hey... You said this is
the dragon's nest, right?

00:14:06.375 --> 00:14:07.042
Yeah.

00:14:07.042 --> 00:14:11.250
If I recall, dragons are nocturnal,
which means it won't be long before...

00:14:16.417 --> 00:14:17.417
It's here!

00:14:21.250 --> 00:14:22.417
H-Hey!

00:14:22.417 --> 00:14:33.750
What?

00:14:33.750 --> 00:14:35.042
Liz, hang on tight!

00:14:44.667 --> 00:14:45.667
We're outside!

00:15:00.583 --> 00:15:02.000
Amazing!

00:15:12.042 --> 00:15:13.625
Kirito!

00:15:14.250 --> 00:15:15.375
You know what?

00:15:15.625 --> 00:15:17.083
What?

00:15:17.750 --> 00:15:19.125
I...

00:15:19.125 --> 00:15:22.042
I like you, Kirito!

00:15:22.458 --> 00:15:24.042
What?

00:15:24.042 --> 00:15:25.542
I can't hear you!

00:15:26.958 --> 00:15:28.833
It's nothing!

00:15:38.292 --> 00:15:39.458
"June 25, 2024"       "Floor 48: Lindas"

00:15:39.458 --> 00:15:41.750
"June 25, 2024"       "Floor 48: Lindas"
You want a one-handed long sword, right?

00:15:41.750 --> 00:15:43.583
Right. I'm counting on you.

00:15:56.250 --> 00:15:58.167
<i>The warmth of Kirito's hands...</i>

00:15:58.625 --> 00:15:59.792
<i>The way I feel.</i>

00:16:00.333 --> 00:16:01.708
<i>It's not an illusion.</i>

00:16:03.000 --> 00:16:05.417
<i>Once I've forged a sword</i>
<i>I can be satisfied with,</i>

00:16:05.417 --> 00:16:07.125
<i>I'm going to tell</i>
<i>him how I feel.</i>

00:16:26.208 --> 00:16:27.875
Its name is Dark Repulsor.

00:16:28.583 --> 00:16:30.583
If I've never heard of it,

00:16:30.583 --> 00:16:33.167
then it isn't in the information
brokers' directory.

00:16:33.958 --> 00:16:35.042
Try it.

00:16:35.042 --> 00:16:36.042
Yeah.

00:16:42.542 --> 00:16:44.292
H-How does it feel?

00:16:44.292 --> 00:16:45.667
Heavy...

00:16:45.667 --> 00:16:46.875
It's a good sword.

00:16:46.875 --> 00:16:47.917
All right!

00:16:48.458 --> 00:16:50.542
It feels like your soul
has been forged into it.

00:16:57.708 --> 00:16:58.958
Now then...

00:16:58.958 --> 00:17:00.833
The job's complete.

00:17:00.833 --> 00:17:02.375
I'll pay you for the sword.

00:17:02.375 --> 00:17:03.500
How much?

00:17:03.500 --> 00:17:05.958
Um, well...

00:17:06.875 --> 00:17:09.250
I don't need any money.

00:17:10.500 --> 00:17:12.042
In exchange...

00:17:13.000 --> 00:17:16.667
I want to be your
exclusive smith, Kirito.

00:17:17.875 --> 00:17:19.375
What does that mean?

00:17:22.667 --> 00:17:23.792
Liz?

00:17:25.208 --> 00:17:27.875
Wh-When you return from the field,

00:17:27.875 --> 00:17:30.292
stop by and let me do
maintenance on your gear.

00:17:30.292 --> 00:17:32.583
Every day, from now on!

00:17:36.250 --> 00:17:37.583
Liz?

00:17:37.583 --> 00:17:39.833
Kirito, I...

00:17:40.917 --> 00:17:42.125
I...

00:17:42.708 --> 00:17:44.667
Liz! I was really worried!

00:17:45.042 --> 00:17:46.875
A-Asuna?

00:17:46.875 --> 00:17:47.875
Liz!

00:17:47.875 --> 00:17:51.000
My message bounced back and
I couldn't track you on the map...

00:17:51.000 --> 00:17:52.917
Where were you last night?

00:17:52.917 --> 00:17:55.958
Sorry, I kind of got
stuck in a dungeon.

00:17:56.458 --> 00:17:57.542
A dungeon?

00:17:57.542 --> 00:17:59.167
Did you go alone?

00:17:59.167 --> 00:18:01.250
No, with him.

00:18:02.125 --> 00:18:03.917
K-Kirito?

00:18:04.292 --> 00:18:06.500
Hey, A-Asuna...

00:18:06.500 --> 00:18:07.875
It's been a while.

00:18:07.875 --> 00:18:09.083
Or maybe it hasn't.

00:18:09.083 --> 00:18:10.250
Two days?

00:18:10.250 --> 00:18:11.750
What a surprise!

00:18:11.750 --> 00:18:13.792
I see, so you dropped
by right away.

00:18:13.792 --> 00:18:16.458
If you'd told me,
I would've come with you.

00:18:16.458 --> 00:18:18.625
Do you know each other,
by any chance?

00:18:19.000 --> 00:18:21.792
Yeah, we're both on
the Assault Team.

00:18:23.500 --> 00:18:25.958
He wanted a powerful sword,

00:18:25.958 --> 00:18:27.875
so I referred him to your shop.

00:18:27.875 --> 00:18:29.417
I see.

00:18:29.417 --> 00:18:32.333
You didn't do anything weird
to my friend, did you?

00:18:32.333 --> 00:18:34.000
O-Of course I didn't!

00:18:34.000 --> 00:18:36.208
The way you just stuttered
is suspicious...

00:18:36.917 --> 00:18:38.333
I almost got killed back there.

00:18:38.333 --> 00:18:40.708
You could show a little compassion!

00:18:40.708 --> 00:18:44.333
That's why I've told you so
often not to fight solo.

00:18:44.917 --> 00:18:46.500
<i>I see.</i>

00:18:46.500 --> 00:18:48.083
<i>So that's it...</i>

00:18:49.208 --> 00:18:52.292
Did this guy say anything
rude to you, Liz?

00:18:54.167 --> 00:18:55.292
Liz?

00:18:58.625 --> 00:19:00.042
Rude? Are you kidding?

00:19:00.042 --> 00:19:03.458
The first thing he did was snap
my best sword in half!

00:19:04.500 --> 00:19:05.875
I-I'm sorry...

00:19:05.875 --> 00:19:08.625
There's no reason for you
to apologize, Asuna.

00:19:10.000 --> 00:19:12.542
Hey, he's weird, but
he's not a bad guy.

00:19:13.042 --> 00:19:15.833
I'll be cheering you on.
So do your best, Asuna.

00:19:16.708 --> 00:19:18.917
I told you it's not like that!

00:19:19.542 --> 00:19:20.250
Liz?

00:19:20.250 --> 00:19:22.958
Sorry, but I have to go
pick up some supplies.

00:19:22.958 --> 00:19:24.083
I'll be right back.

00:19:24.833 --> 00:19:26.458
What about the shop?

00:19:26.458 --> 00:19:28.958
You two, hold down the fort!
I'm counting on you!

00:19:29.833 --> 00:19:31.458
Wait, Liz!

00:19:49.458 --> 00:19:50.792
Lisbeth...

00:19:57.125 --> 00:19:59.417
You shouldn't have come here now.

00:20:02.250 --> 00:20:04.167
Just a little longer...

00:20:04.167 --> 00:20:07.333
...and I would've gone back to
my usual cheerful self...

00:20:07.708 --> 00:20:08.708
Liz...

00:20:09.958 --> 00:20:11.875
How'd you know I was here?

00:20:16.250 --> 00:20:19.333
I scanned the whole town
for you from up there.

00:20:20.167 --> 00:20:22.625
You always do the craziest things.

00:20:28.625 --> 00:20:31.625
Sorry... I'm fine.

00:20:32.125 --> 00:20:35.708
I'm not used to adventures,
so I think it just shook me up inside...

00:20:36.125 --> 00:20:37.208
So...

00:20:38.500 --> 00:20:43.333
Forget everything I said.

00:20:44.958 --> 00:20:48.042
I want to thank you.

00:20:49.250 --> 00:20:50.333
I've always...

00:20:50.917 --> 00:20:56.125
...always thought it would be better
to die than to survive alone...

00:20:56.708 --> 00:20:58.375
I've honestly always believed that.

00:20:59.792 --> 00:21:00.833
Kirito?

00:21:01.458 --> 00:21:03.875
But when we fell in that hole,

00:21:03.875 --> 00:21:06.042
I was glad that
we both made it.

00:21:06.833 --> 00:21:12.083
I realized that everyone is striving
to stay alive. Myself included.

00:21:12.833 --> 00:21:15.667
So thank you, Liz.

00:21:16.375 --> 00:21:17.500
Same here...

00:21:18.208 --> 00:21:21.208
I was always looking
for something too!

00:21:21.208 --> 00:21:23.708
Something real in this world...

00:21:25.500 --> 00:21:26.833
For me,

00:21:27.833 --> 00:21:30.833
the warmth of your hand...
that was real.

00:21:35.542 --> 00:21:38.917
Tell Asuna what you just told me.

00:21:39.250 --> 00:21:40.333
Liz...

00:21:40.333 --> 00:21:41.750
I'm fine!

00:21:42.917 --> 00:21:45.958
This warmth will still
linger for a while.

00:21:47.083 --> 00:21:49.833
So... please...

00:21:50.667 --> 00:21:53.208
End this world, Kirito.

00:21:54.333 --> 00:21:57.458
Until then, I'm sure
that I can hang on!

00:21:58.958 --> 00:22:00.125
I promise.

00:22:00.667 --> 00:22:02.375
I'll clear this game,
no matter what.

00:22:06.500 --> 00:22:08.583
If you need your weapons
or equipment repaired,

00:22:08.583 --> 00:22:09.958
come by anytime.

00:22:09.958 --> 00:22:11.458
Sure.

00:22:11.458 --> 00:22:14.792
Please continue to support
Lisbeth's Smith Shop!

00:22:30.125 --> 00:22:41.583
<i>The tolling of the faraway bells</i>
<i>sounded a little lonely to me</i>

00:22:41.917 --> 00:22:53.458
<i>So I tried harder, one more time,</i>
<i>this time soaring higher, all the way up</i>

00:22:53.875 --> 00:22:59.417
<i>Neither this reality that just keeps repeating itself</i>

00:22:59.750 --> 00:23:05.208
<i>Nor all my wishes, as numerous as the stars</i>

00:23:05.625 --> 00:23:10.625
<i>Now that I've found the tomorrow</i>
<i>I should strive for</i>

00:23:10.958 --> 00:23:15.917
<i>None of them can overcome these feelings of mine</i>

00:23:16.250 --> 00:23:22.708
<i>A world without end, opening up before my eyes</i>

00:23:23.042 --> 00:23:26.667
<i>Even if it's no more than a dream</i>

00:23:27.250 --> 00:23:34.000
<i>Even if I'm still lost, deep in my heart, it is strong</i>

00:23:34.333 --> 00:23:39.792
<i>Echoing forever and ever</i>

00:23:40.125 --> 00:23:46.292
<i>Shining softly, ever so softly</i>

00:23:47.083 --> 00:23:53.195
Next Time: "The Sword Dance
of Black and White."
